# 4. 予想外のお客様

Staff: Let's cut there for now!
Staff: We'll do the close-up of the parfait now, so let's get a light on it! Oh, let's get a napkin with the cafe's logo to go with that shot!
Minori: I feel like the crew's working constantly during these shoots even when we're on break...
Airi: Yeah, only the personalities get to rest. I honestly can't thank them enough for all their hard work.
Shizuku: Short segments like this one will only end up being a few minutes long, but it takes an entire day to film it.
Haruka: And it's our job to make this show as fun as possible. So, let's do our best and make the most of what the crew is doing for us.
Minori: Yeah, let's!
???: I'm so glad we were able to make a reservation!
???: You heard about how this cafe's doing a shoot today because it's been going so viral on social media, right?
???: Yeah. And the staff was so polite about us visiting. I hope we don't startle everyone else here too much.
???: I mean, we are a pretty rowdy bunch. I sorta think they have every right to feel that way.
Shizuku: The cafe's become much livelier all of a sudden...
Minori: Oh, I think that's the group the manager was talking about!
Airi: We should be fine because we have these curtains up, but we still need to be on our best behavior.
Minori: Right!
Minori: Still, it's pretty rare for groups to make reservations for here. I wonder what they're...
Minori: Huh?! That group of customers...
Airi: What's wrong, Minori? Wait, huh?
???: I can't wait. I'm starved.
???: Order as much as you like. We warned this cafe beforehand that we'd be coming.
???: Awesome! And it's like they came up with these Mount Everest sized menu items just for us! Thanks, Fujin! You always find the best places!
???: Hehe. Anytime. I mean, what's better than stuffing our faces in sweets after doing an event?
Airi: H-Hey, isn't that the female professional wrestler, Riser☆Fujin?!
Shizuku: Oh, is she famous...?
Minori: She's really popular on PicShare! She has like 1.5 million followers!
Minori: Lately, everyone's been talking about how she's been helping wrestling teams and organizations who've fallen on hard times get back on their feet!
Haruka: Oh, I had no idea she was so popular...
Minori: Yeah, and she's famous for being a huge sweets connoisseur. She's even come up with some for a few convenience stores...
Minori: But she's most famous for taking other wrestlers from her organization out after big matches to tackle mountains of sweets.
Shizuku: Wait...
Haruka: Mountains of...
Fujin: Okay, let's order...
Fujin: Excuse me! To start, we'd like ten of your Mount Everest strawberry parfaits and eight of your seasonal waffles!
Airi: U-Uhh, wow...
Airi: This is turning into a pretty big test for the staff...
Staff: Okay, break's over! Let's resume our shoot!
Minori: W-W-We have to get back to work!
Shizuku: I hope Mizuki and Saki are going to be okay...
Airi: We can't do much to help right now, so we'll just have to believe that they will be...
Airi: You've got this, you two...!
Saki: Huff... Huff... Huff...
Kitchen Staff Member: I've got two plates of waffles ready here!
Saki: I've got three! Mizuki, how are you doing on your end...?!
Mizuki: G-Gimme a sec...! I'm still not done with the first three I got!
Mizuki: Wait... Five dollops of whipped cream, right...? Two, three, four, five.
Mizuki: Okay, done!
Mizuki: Heh heh heh. Not bad if I do say so myself!
Mizuki: I'll start working on the ones we just got!
Saki: Really?! I'm just about done making my batch, so I'll help you with the whipped cream and...
Mizuki: Huh...? D-Did something happen?
Saki: The cream on the edge of this plate sort of fell apart...
Mizuki: Wait...
Mizuki: Y-Yeah, it's a little lower than the other ones... But is it gonna be that big of a problem?
Mizuki: I mean, the bow in the middle of this one looks better than any of the other ones...
Saki: Nope, do it again!
Mizuki: Whaat?! But I thought it turned out really well!
Saki: Yes, I know it's really hard to get everything to look all nice and pretty when things are super busy. Which makes cutting corners all the more tempting...
Saki: Each plate may be one out of the many for us, but each one means everything to our customers!
Saki: So, we have to give each plate the love it deserves regardless of how busy things get...
Saki: That's the motto of carino/carina!
Mizuki: Give each plate... The love it deserves...
Mizuki: Yeah, you're right... I also obsess over the tiniest stuff whenever I'm making something.
Saki: Hehe. I'm glad you understand.
Saki: The first time our boss told me that, I also thought it was a really strict rule.
Saki: But I began to understand the reasoning behind it after seeing the smiles on all our customers' faces.
Mizuki: Yeah...
Mizuki: If you're making something for someone, you should do everything you can for it. Otherwise, the person receiving it won't understand what you were trying to do...
Mizuki: Okay.
Mizuki: I'll start over! I'm gonna make it look gorgeous this time!
Saki: Yeah, that's what I like to hear♪
Saki: Then, I'll show you how to gussy up the whipped cream. For the ones that fell apart slightly, just do this and...
Mizuki: Whoa, that's so cool! They look perfect now!
Saki: I know, right? You just have to do this now if something goes wrong.
Saki: So, let's try to get those orders out and...
Fujin: Oh, excuse me! We'd like five more plates of your mega pudding a la mode!
Saki: E...
Saki & Mizuki: Eeeeeepp!!!
Haruka: Was that a scream I just heard...?
Airi: (I really hope Mizuki and Saki are okay...)
Airi: (I wish we could lend them a hand...)
Manager: A-Anyway... Including our parfaits, we've put quite a lot of thought into each of our menu items. As a result, our customers have been giving us some very nice reviews.
Airi: (Oh, that's right...! Now's our chance to...)
Airi: I agree! The parfaits are one thing, but the rest of the menu also looks amazing! I've even been hearing some of the other customers ordering some of these items...
Airi: Which gave me an idea...
